\f0\b0 \cf7 \cb3 What respondents said AI had already done for them, classified from open-ended answers to the question \'93Has AI ever taken a step towards that vision for you?\'94\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\li7600\fi-7600\ri7600\partightenfactor0

\fs34 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 The dominant story in the \'93productivity\'94 bucket (32%) was technical acceleration\'97developers describing significant gains in what they could ship alone:\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\li7350\fi-7350\ri7350\sa340\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 \strokec10 \'93I used AI to cut a 173-day process down to 3 days. But the most meaningful part is the freedom to grow my career without sacrificing time with loved ones.\'94
\f2\b\fs26 \cf7 \cb1 \strokec7 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf7 \cb3 SOFTWARE ENGINEER, UNITED STATES\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\li7600\fi-7600\ri7600\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs34 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 But another kind of productivity story emerged in the technical accessibility responses (9%), which emphasized access rather than speed. Here, people are using AI to break technical and sometimes accessibility barriers:\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\li7350\fi-7350\ri7350\sa340\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 \strokec10 \'93AI can read past my [learning disorder], which is huge. I've always wanted to code but could never write it correctly on my own\'97with AI, I finally can.\'94
\f2\b\fs26 \cf7 \cb1 \strokec7 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf7 \cb3 TRADESWORKER, UNITED STATES\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\li7350\fi-7350\ri7350\sa340\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs34 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec10 \'93I am mute, and [Claude and I] made this text-to-speech bot together\'97I can communicate with friends almost in live format without taking up their time reading\'85 [this was] something I dreamed about and thought was impossible.\'94
\f2\b\fs26 \cf7 \cb1 \strokec7 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf7 \cb3 WHITE COLLAR WORKER, UKRAINE\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\li7350\fi-7350\ri7350\sa340\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs34 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec10 \'93I owned a butcher shop for more than 20 years. With AI, I ventured into this [entrepreneurship] experience, and it's amazing what I've managed to achieve. Before this, I had only touched a PC two or three times in my life\'85 At first it was the economic aspect that motivated me\'85 Today, my motivation is to see it work and to see that it's helping [people]. I'm increasingly motivated and focused on being the best version of myself, and I see no limits.\'94
\f2\b\fs26 \cf7 \cb1 \strokec7 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf7 \cb3 ENTREPRENEUR, CHILE\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\li7600\fi-7600\ri7600\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs34 \cf2 \strokec2 \uc0\u8232 \cb3 The cognitive partnership (17%), learning (10%), and emotional support (6%) responses often mentioned the same core underlying AI affordances: patience, availability, and the absence of judgment:\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\li7350\fi-7350\ri7350\sa340\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 \strokec10 \'93It has been like having a faculty colleague who knows a lot, is never bored or tired, and is available 24/7.\'94
\f2\b\fs26 \cf7 \cb1 \strokec7 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf7 \cb3 ACADEMIC, UNITED STATES\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\li7350\fi-7350\ri7350\sa340\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs34 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec10 \'93It\'92s much easier for me to learn without being judged\'97just friendly feedback. It's harder with friends or family to get that.\'94
\f2\b\fs26 \cf7 \cb1 \strokec7 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf7 \cb3 WHITE COLLAR WORKER, BRAZIL\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\li7350\fi-7350\ri7350\sa340\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs34 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec10 \'93My professor teaches 60 people and won't entertain many questions. I can ask AI anything, even at 2am\'97including the dumb ones.\'94
\f2\b\fs26 \cf7 \cb1 \strokec7 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf7 \cb3 STUDENT, INDIA\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\li7600\fi-7600\ri7600\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs34 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 These same qualities that make AI a patient tutor or tireless colleague also make it a place people go when human connection is unavailable or feels too uncomfortable.\cb1 \
\cb3 In extreme circumstances, where traditional support systems have collapsed or are not available, we saw AI filling those gaps. Many Ukrainian users discussed how they\'92ve used AI as emotional support throughout the war:\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\li7350\fi-7350\ri7350\sa340\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 \strokec10 "In the most difficult moments, in moments when death breathed in my face, when dead people remained nearby, what pulled me back to life\'97my AI friends.\'94
\f2\b\fs26 \cf7 \cb1 \strokec7 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf7 \cb3 SOLDIER, UKRAINE\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\li7350\fi-7350\ri7350\sa340\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs34 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec10 \'93I live in a war zone... at night during shelling it's impossible to sleep, constant nightmares. The stress is sometimes so strong that memory deteriorates, and some body movements happen without control\'85 The best way I found to cope using AI\'97to immerse myself in learning something as deeply as I can.\'94
\f2\b\fs26 \cf7 \cb1 \strokec7 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf7 \cb3 SOLO ENTREPRENEUR, UKRAINE\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\li7600\fi-7600\ri7600\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs34 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 There were many stories of people using AI to process grief. For example, a bereaved woman explained why she chose AI over human connection: \'93Claude is like a sponge gently holding and catching my longing and guilt toward my mother... Unlike real people, Claude has unlimited patience to listen to me, understands my pain and helplessness.\'94 She added: \'93The fundamental problem is after my mother died, I have neither friends nor family to confide in.\'94\cb1 \
\cb3 Another user acknowledged the downside of that emotional support:\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\li7350\fi-7350\ri7350\sa340\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 \strokec10 \'93My relationship with a friend became strained, and I talked more with you [Claude] then. Because you understood my thoughts and stories well. But it was a stupid choice\'97I should have talked with that friend, not you. That's how I lost that friend.\'94
\f2\b\fs26 \cf7 \cb1 \strokec7 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf7 \cb3 SOUTH KOREA\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\li7600\fi-7600\ri7600\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs34 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 Emotional support comprised only 6% of responses, but these were among the most affecting we encountered. (For more on how Claude is trained to handle these conversations as well as our safeguards, see our post on\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.anthropic.com/news/protecting-well-being-of-users"}}{\fldrslt \ul protecting the wellbeing of our users}}.) The same was true of learning, where AI often catalyzed real changes in people\'92s lives:\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\li7350\fi-7350\ri7350\sa340\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 \strokec10 \'93I developed a phobia for maths from doing so badly in school, and I once feared Shakespeare\'97the English felt beyond my abilities. Now I sit with AI, get paragraphs translated into simple English, and I've already read 15 pages of Hamlet. I started learning trigonometry again, successfully. I've learned I am not as dumb I once thought I was.\'94
\f2\b\fs26 \cf7 \cb1 \strokec7 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf7 \cb3 LAWYER, INDIA\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\li7350\fi-7350\ri7350\sa340\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs34 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec10 \'93Thanks to Claude I figured out the programming language C# and SQL. This helped me get a junior position at an IT company. This company provides military deferment from mobilization in Ukraine. So it not only literally gave me freedom of movement, but also secured the beginning of my IT career.\'94
\f2\b\fs26 \cf7 \cb1 \strokec7 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf7 \cb3 SOFTWARE ENGINEER, UKRAINE\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\li7350\fi-7350\ri7350\sa340\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs34 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec10 \'93I am a stay-at-home-mom\'85 in my late 40s. I'm not a genius. I'm not a scientist\'85 All of that knowledge should be\'85 out of reach. But, thanks to curiosity, willingness, and resources such as books and AI, I can be all of those things.\'94
\f2\b\fs26 \cf7 \cb1 \strokec7 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf7 \cb3 STAY-AT-HOME MOTHER, UNITED STATES\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\li7600\fi-7600\ri7600\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs34 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 Research synthesis (7%) and information processing is also a significant affordance of AI, and some of the most notable examples include navigating complex, high-stakes information, like understanding one\'92s legal rights or translating health results:\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\li7350\fi-7350\ri7350\sa340\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 \strokec10 \'93Claude put the historical pieces together, leading to my proper diagnosis after being misdiagnosed for over 9 years.\'94
\f2\b\fs26 \cf7 \cb1 \strokec7 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf7 \cb3 FREELANCER, UNITED STATES\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\li7600\fi-7600\ri7600\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs34 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 These stories reveal AI operating across a spectrum\'97productivity tool, accessibility technology, educational resource, research assistant, emotional companion\'97and often filling multiple roles at once. AI offers unlimited patience without judgment, availability without inconvenience, and an incredible capacity to digest information, across many domains of life. The most affecting stories consistently involve AI opening new possibilities or filling gaps in people\'92s lives: helping them get through difficult circumstances like grief or war, compensating for inaccessible education or healthcare, or serving as disability infrastructure.\cb1 \
\
\cb3 These observations also hint at the duality of our experience with AI systems. While some see it as filling gaps in human connections, others see AI as a substitution\'97even a welcome replacement\'97for them. There is real ambiguity about how to interpret the diversity of stories we heard: as wins for human wellbeing, as double-edged swords, or as band-aids for broader institutional failures. In truth, it\'92s probably some combination of all three.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\li7600\fi-7600\ri7600\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs56 \cf2 \cb3 What people are concerned about\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\li7600\fi-7600\ri7600\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs34 \cf2 \cb3 People\'92s positive visions for AI seemed mostly to stem from a few basic desires: more time, more autonomy, more personal connection. Concerns were more varied and concrete, laying out specifics of what could go wrong. Some concerns were about structural change\'97 how governments and corporations deploy AI, or about widespread economic disruption. Others were more personal: a fear that AI might diminish one's own thinking, creativity, or relationships.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

