\f2\b\fs56 \cf2 \strokec2 Looking forward\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\li7600\fi-7600\ri7600\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs34 \cf2 \cb3 These interviews give us a sense of what people want from AI broadly, which informs how we build Claude. They reinforced the importance of work we're already doing, and pointed us toward new questions to ask.\cb1 \
\cb3 Most of the visions people described, ranging from personal transformation to cognitive support, collapse into an underlying desire: that AI helps them live\'a0
\f4\i better
\f0\i0 , not simply work\'a0
\f4\i faster
\f0\i0 . Our next\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.anthropic.com/research/anthropic-interviewer"}}{\fldrslt \ul Anthropic Interviewer}}\'a0study, launching shortly to a small subset of Claude users, focuses on Claude\'92s effects on people\'92s wellbeing over time: whether Claude is actually making people's lives better in the ways they want, and how it could do so more effectively.\cb1 \
\cb3 Additionally, nearly one in ten people described a positive vision of societal transformation\'97AI to cure diseases, democratize expertise, and strengthen institutions. Through our Beneficial Deployments program, we\'92re collaborating with our\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.anthropic.com/news/ai-for-science-program"}}{\fldrslt \ul AI for Science}}\'a0and\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.anthropic.com/news/claude-for-nonprofits"}}{\fldrslt \ul nonprofit}}\'a0partners to understand how they use Claude and where it still needs to improve, to close the gap between the societal transformations people envision and today's reality. We also take some of the most-cited concerns\'97e.g. around negative economic impacts of AI\'97seriously, as signals around which we are designing further research and updating our\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.anthropic.com/research/economic-policy-responses"}}{\fldrslt \ul thinking}}.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\li7600\fi-7600\ri7600\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs56 \cf2 \cb3 Conclusion\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\li7600\fi-7600\ri7600\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs34 \cf2 \cb3 AI poses both opportunities and risks. This is true\'97but also, at this point, a clich\'e9. One of our goals for this research is to offer a complement to the abstractions we all tend to use in speaking about AI; to capture the texture that more vividly renders exactly how we are already experiencing these opportunities and risks worldwide. Before this research, it was hard for us to see any kind of broad qualitative picture\'97the way AI has already become intertwined with people\'92s lives, nurturing aspirations but also feeding anxieties; how it feels to exist in a world on the precipice of sweeping technological change.\cb1 \
\cb3 This is a new form of social science. It is qualitative research at a massive scale, and we\'92re in the early stages of learning how to do it. Surveys and usage\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.anthropic.com/economic-index"}}{\fldrslt \ul analysis}}\'a0tell us\'a0
\f4\i what
\f0\i0 \'a0people are doing with AI, but the open-ended interview format helps us get at\'a0
\f4\i why
\f0\i0 . Conducting this research has moved us and challenged us. We did not expect so many deep, open, and thoughtful responses. By far the most common reflection from our team was that it was viscerally moving to see Claude impacting people\'92s lives for the better, and equally motivating to hear their concerns.\cb1 \
\cb3 We don\'92t usually get to hear from small business owners around the world using Claude to reclaim time to spend with their young children or aging parents, or from truck drivers and butchers building new careers with the help of Claude, or from teachers in under-resourced schools using Claude to surpass what they achieved when they taught in well-funded schools. We were surprised by the incredible volume of people who have been supported by Claude in their educational or personal growth endeavors, and the people finding in AI freedom from judgment in a way they hadn\'92t experienced before. We were equally gripped by the fears and downsides\'97people saying that the same availability making Claude useful is what makes it hard to put down, or knowledge workers worrying about outrunning AI\'92s economic impact. When you come into contact with this much raw human experience, it knocks you sideways. The usefulness is real, and the question for all of us is how to claim the benefits without incurring undue costs.\cb1 \
\cb3 To the 81,000 people who took the time to speak with us: thank you. It has been striking, and humbling, to see Claude form the basis of so many people\'92s hopes, dreams, and fears. These interviews remind us what it means, and what it takes, to build AI that benefits everyone.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

